race.description: Xxxx Gold Snake Gully Cup Handicap
race.comment: Strong contest with plenty of different form angles. MONEY TEAM (3) progressive gelding who comes out of a strong rating race when collared late for a respectable fourth over 1200m at Randwick in BM84 class. Lobs into the stalking position and can assert his class late. TICKLEBELLY (9) peaking at the right time and indicated a win was imminent when a tiring third over 1300m to So You Pence at Randwick. Has a solid record here and goes close. VILLASAURUS (17) backed off the map on resumption when saluting in good style over 1400m at Wagga. Goes equally as well second-up and should get cover from the draw. BELLEISTIC KIDS (8) ran second in this race in 2023 and recent efforts in town have been satisfactory. Will push forward and has the ability to run into the minor money.
